.TH JTUTIL-MD5 "1" "April 2026" "jtutil-md5 manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-md5 \- Refresh md5.md checksums for MRA files
.SH DESCRIPTION
The asm_md5 attribute in MRA files indicate the right sum for all the
.IP
data in the file. This is affected by file order and interleaving. Keeping track
of asm_md5 is useful to catch unintentional changes in MRA files
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil md5 [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-compare\fR string
json file to compare with
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for md5
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-path\fR string
path to the mra folder to explore (default "/nobackup/jtmisc/jtbin")
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose
